24
00:02:16,779 --> 00:02:19,504
Pay attention to the verb form.

25
00:02:20,592 --> 00:02:23,760
What suggestions did you make? Of\h\h

26
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:28,000
course, there are many possible\h
answers! Here are some examples.

27
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:38,240
It’s a beautiful day. Let’s go to the beach.
I’m hungry. How about going out for a pizza?\h

28
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:44,400
I’m free this morning. Why\h
don’t we go to the market?\h

29
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:50,794
There’s a movie on channel 4. Shall we watch it?

30
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,640
Were your suggestions the same as mine?

31
00:02:57,360 --> 00:03:03,840
Now, let’s see phases you can use to\h
accept a suggestion. In the dialogue, you heard:

32
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,720
There are many other phrases you could use.\h\h

33
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:14,560
You could just say something simple\h
like ‘yeah’ or ‘yeah, why not?’\h

34
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:21,600
If you want to sound a little less\h
casual, you could say something like\h\h

35
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:24,960
‘I would like that’ or ‘That\h
sounds like a good idea.’\h

36
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:33,040
But, what if you don’t want to do what the\h
other person is suggesting? Let’s look.

37
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:42,000
Sometimes, even though it’s a bit difficult,\h
you’ve got to reject a suggestion have to\h\h

38
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,200
say ‘no’ to people.

39
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:50,640
In this case, it’s important to be\h
polite, even if you’re talking to a friend.

40
00:03:52,720 --> 00:04:00,880
Let’s see a dialogue which shows you how *not*\h
to do this. Listen and try to find the problems.

41
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:05,520
It’s a beautiful day. Shall we go out somewhere?\h

42
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:08,000
No, I don’t want to.
Oh, come on!\h\h

43
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:12,800
Why don’t we go for a walk along the river?
What an awful idea.\h

44
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:17,760
Well, let’s go somewhere for some lunch.
No, let’s not.\h

45
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:23,040
Well, how about watching a movie together?
Count me out.

46
00:04:23,987 --> 00:04:24,960
What do you think?\h

47
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:31,360
You *could* use phrases like this\h
to reject someone else’s suggestion…\h

48
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:36,640
but it doesn’t sound polite.

49
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:43,000
So,\h\hhow could we improve them? Listen\h
again and see the difference.

50
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:48,560
It’s a beautiful day. Shall we go out somewhere?
I’d rather not, if you don’t mind.\h

51
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:52,160
Oh, come on! Why don’t we go\h
for a walk along the river?\h

52
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:58,480
I don’t really feel like it, I’m afraid.
Well, let’s go somewhere for some lunch.\h

53
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,274
Maybe another time.

54
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:09,840
Did you hear the four polite phrases\h
you can use to say ‘no’ to a suggestion?\h

55
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,291
Let’s look together.

56
00:05:13,702 --> 00:05:18,560
These are polite ways to reject a suggestion.

57
00:05:19,422 --> 00:05:25,840
The phrase – ‘can I take a rain check?’\h
– means that you want to do something, but\h\h

58
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:29,699
not right now. You’ll do it another time.

59
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:37,840
It’s a lovely day. Why don’t we go shopping?\h

60
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:45,760
Maybe another time. I’ve got a lot to do today.
How about going for a walk? Maybe along the river?\h

61
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:50,240
I don’t really feel like it,\h
I’m afraid. I’m a bit tired.\h

62
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:55,440
Well, let’s go somewhere for lunch.
I’d rather not, if you don’t mind.\h\h

63
00:05:55,440 --> 00:06:00,560
I’m not very hungry right now.
Then how about going to the park?\h

64
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:03,520
Can I take a rain check? I’m\h
a bit busy at the moment.

65
00:06:04,536 --> 00:06:05,544
When you say\h\h

66
